---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Origami | Work | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer & Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Origami</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in 2013, Origami was building mobile payment solutions for Japan's
      cash-dominant market. The startup launched QR-code payments in 2015 and
      worked with partners including convenience stores and restaurants to bring
      digital payments to Japanese consumers.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      When I moved to Japan in 2015, I joined Origami during their pivot from
      ecommerce to mobile payments. I worked on designing payment experiences in
      a market where consumers were unsure of digital payments.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Pay</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Working closely with an iOS engineer while receiving ongoing feedback from
      the CEO, I prototyped in Swift a way to pay with Bluetooth. Something that
      that made purchases feel more fun than cash.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I also designed the customer ratings feature for these in-store
      experiences. Giving store owners insights about customer preferences that
      helped them improve service beyond what purchase history alone could
      reveal.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-pay.png"
      alt="Mobile payment flow optimized for Japanese market preferences."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-ipad-payment.png"
      alt="Mobile payment flow optimized for Japanese market preferences."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Navigation</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      With pop-up promotions happening in malls across the country, we needed
      people to experience payments without account creation barriers. I
      redesigned the navigation to prioritize core functions. These were
      payments, cards, and receipts.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We also added guest browsing so hoppers could immediately understand the
      value without signing up.
    </Text>
    <Group>
      <Image
        src="/images/work/origami-navigation.png"
        alt="Navigation system designed for single-handed mobile usage patterns."
        class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
        lightbox={true}
      />
    </Group>
  </Group>
</Layout>
